The course provides an overview of the key concepts and theories of semantics (concept of meaning; structure of word meaning: signification, denotation, referent; semantic relationships of a word in the language: polysemy, homonymy, synonymy, antonymy; component meaning analysis) and the concepts and theories of pragmatics (deixis; implication; cooperative principle; speech act theory; courtesy theory; conversation analysis; discourse analysis). The course examines the application of major theories in practical analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduce the semantics and pragmatics disciplines by providing students with a comprehensive overview of key concepts in semantics and pragmatics and important analytical techniquesLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) can identify and explain the key concepts of semantics and pragmatics; 2) knows semantic theories about the structure of meaning in a word; 3) knows pragmatic theories about the construction of interactive meaning; 4) is able to analyze text using methods of disciplinary analysis.
